<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Thorax</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Prothorax nota with wrinkles, those developed on spino-pleural area. Meso- and metanotum with wrinkles on marginal area, spino-pleural area smooth. Thoracic setae sparse, short and blunt, with small setal tubercles; pronotum with two pairs of spinal setae, arranged in anterior and posterior pairs, one pair of pleural and one pair of marginal setae; meso- and metanotum each with one pair of spinal, one pair of pleural setae, two pairs of marginal setae, respectively. Legs normal, smooth. Setae on 2/3 distal part of femora and tibiae, short and blunt; hind tibiae with a row of short and blunt setae dorsally on the middle (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 20" captionStartId="F20" captionText="Figure 20. Aspidophorodon (Eoessigia) obtusirostre Qiao &amp; Xu, sp. nov. Apterous viviparous female A dorsal view of body B dorsal view of head C antenna D ultimate rostral segment E hind tibia and tarsi F siphunculus G spinal process of abdominal tergite VIII H cauda I anal plate J genital plate. Scale bars: 0.10 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.77912.figure20" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/702355" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">20E</figureCitation>
). First tarsal chaetotaxy: 3, 2, 2. Second tarsal segments slightly imbricated.
</paragraph>
